premise_source_doc_sentence: Several proofs of the theorem , beginning with a proof due to Brauer and John Tate , show that the trivial character is in the analogously defined ideal I *  (  G  )  of Char *  (  G  )  by concentrating attention on one prime p at a time , and constructing integer-valued elements of I *  (  G  )  which differ  (  elementwise  )  from the trivial character by  (  integer multiples of  )  a sufficiently high power of p .
